<subsection xml:id="subsec-surface-area-of-pyramids">
    <title>Surface area of pyramids</title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
            A <m>\textbf{Pyramid}</m> is a solid with a polygonal
            base and slanting sides that meet at a
            common apex.
        </p>
        <p>
            The base can be a triangle, square, or other 
            polygon. The number of triangular faces depends on the shape of the base.
        </p>
        <p>
            For <m>\textbf{example}</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            A square-based pyramid has <m>1</m> square base and 4 triangular faces.
        </p>
        <p>
            The surface area of a <m>\textbf{Pyramid}</m> is the sum of the area of the
            slanting faces and the area of the base.
        </p>
        <p>
            Lets explore how to calculate the surface area of pyramids with different bases.
        </p>
        
    </introduction>


